<b>awaqeded</b> for <b>www.addic7ed.com</b>.

15:15.434 --> 15:17.324
STEVIE: <i>Mom? Dad?</i>

15:21.854 --> 15:22.853
ELIZABETH (laughs): Hey.

15:22.854 --> 15:23.519
Hi.

15:23.520 --> 15:24.284
HENRY: Hey.

15:25.854 --> 15:27.603
So... we're engaged.

15:27.604 --> 15:29.893
- (gasps)
- You're kidding.

15:29.894 --> 15:30.933
Wow!

15:30.934 --> 15:33.763
Hey, that's great.

15:33.764 --> 15:34.933
I asked and she said yes.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.204
- Oh! - Ah!
- (laughing)

15:37.564 --> 15:39.223
STEVIE: Well, he didn't just ask me.

15:39.224 --> 15:41.223
- He put this ring in the parfait,
- Ring?

15:41.224 --> 15:42.473
and I almost choked on it.

15:42.474 --> 15:43.513
- Ring?
- Let me see.

15:43.514 --> 15:44.803
Yeah, I forgot.

15:44.804 --> 15:47.473
Um, yeah, and he got down
on one knee and-and...

15:47.474 --> 15:49.473
(laughing): the whole
restaurant was watching.

15:49.474 --> 15:51.853
- Oh!
- They all applauded when I said yes.

15:51.854 --> 15:53.853
Wow, because you said yes.

15:53.854 --> 15:55.893
Of course you did, with that ring.

15:55.894 --> 15:57.303
Oh, it's a family heirloom.

15:57.304 --> 15:58.119
Yeah.

15:58.120 --> 15:58.973
Oh. Mm!

15:58.974 --> 16:00.643
Well, congratulations.

16:00.644 --> 16:02.183
Uh, that...

16:02.184 --> 16:03.847
We-we couldn't be
happier for you, really.

16:03.848 --> 16:05.473
And we're sure the date is way off.

16:05.474 --> 16:07.563
'Cause you got to finish
college and law school.

16:07.564 --> 16:09.827
Oh, why are we...? We don't
need to think about that now.

16:09.828 --> 16:10.893
Let's not.

16:10.894 --> 16:12.803
Let's... let's have that champagne.

16:12.804 --> 16:14.473
Well, actually, it's not that far.

16:14.474 --> 16:17.303
We were thinking we-we might
have it in DC at the courthouse.

16:17.304 --> 16:18.887
STEVIE: Yeah, we-we
already have a date.

16:18.888 --> 16:20.013
It's, uh, this weekend.

16:20.014 --> 16:20.764
Wow!

16:20.765 --> 16:21.513
Yeah.

16:21.514 --> 16:22.853
(cell phone rings)

16:22.854 --> 16:25.013
Uh, sorry, that's, um, it's my parents.

16:25.014 --> 16:26.683
- We haven't told them yet. I...
- Oh yeah, um...

16:26.684 --> 16:28.353
- Oh, yeah, go, go, go.
- STEVIE: We'll be back in one...

16:28.354 --> 16:29.353
- We'll... One sec.
- JARETH: Hi, Mum.

16:29.354 --> 16:30.353
Um, just a minute.

16:30.354 --> 16:31.164
(Elizabeth sighs)

16:31.165 --> 16:32.013
(chuckles)

16:32.014 --> 16:34.433
(whispering): Are we united
that this is too fast?

16:34.434 --> 16:36.393
(whispering): Way too fast.

16:36.394 --> 16:38.393
MIKE: Okay, I've done my homework,

16:38.394 --> 16:40.263
and here's where we are.

16:40.264 --> 16:42.723
First up, Albert Kopp,
deputy secretary under Marsh,

16:42.724 --> 16:45.579
now works in the private
sector consulting for an NGO.

16:45.580 --> 16:48.248
I knew him well.

16:48.249 --> 16:50.208
(sighs) The plagiarism
scandal from years ago

16:50.209 --> 16:51.288
is probably behind him,

16:51.289 --> 16:54.868
but the "everyone in
bureaucracy hated him" scandal

16:54.869 --> 16:56.368
most likely is not.

16:56.369 --> 16:59.708
I doubt Dalton would hoist
him on the rank and file.

16:59.709 --> 17:01.038
Lloyd Frost.

17:01.039 --> 17:03.078
Former high-ranking military officer,

17:03.079 --> 17:06.657
two-term congressman and
ex-ambassador to Indonesia.

17:06.659 --> 17:08.082
Frost would never relocate to DC...

17:08.083 --> 17:10.208
Because his mistress lives in San Diego.

17:10.209 --> 17:11.208
Yes, I know.

17:11.209 --> 17:13.208
Okay.

17:13.209 --> 17:15.417
Calvin Hastings, former
ambassador to the UN.

17:15.419 --> 17:16.882
Plenty of foreign policy experience.

17:16.883 --> 17:18.117
And he's from a purple state,

17:18.118 --> 17:20.417
so his constituency
would be useful to Dalton.

17:20.419 --> 17:21.748
Uh-huh.

17:21.749 --> 17:23.078
His wife is a veteran.

17:23.079 --> 17:25.417
They have three beautiful children.

17:25.419 --> 17:29.748
And he has a history of
outside-the-box thinking.

17:29.749 --> 17:32.788
If anything, he's a
Secretary McCord 2.0.

17:32.789 --> 17:34.158
And he's clean.

17:34.159 --> 17:36.658
Well...

17:36.659 --> 17:38.328
if you can't find dirt
on him, nobody can.

17:38.329 --> 17:41.208
Thank you.

17:41.209 --> 17:42.328
Frankly, I think he'd make

17:42.329 --> 17:44.828
a more useful secretary than Elizabeth.

17:44.829 --> 17:46.708
Because he's from a swing state.

17:46.709 --> 17:47.929
Relax.

17:52.159 --> 17:54.158
I miss my shoes.

17:54.159 --> 17:56.708
ELIZABETH: <i>Well, that was brutal.</i>

17:56.709 --> 18:01.708
All that champagne and terrible ideas.

18:01.709 --> 18:04.328
My face hurts from fake smiling.

18:04.329 --> 18:06.418
How do you think my tongue
feels from me biting it?

18:06.419 --> 18:08.288
She's going to put school

18:08.289 --> 18:10.158
on hold and maybe

18:10.159 --> 18:13.748
find work in a pub... she did say pub.

18:13.749 --> 18:17.708
For the experience of immersing herself

18:17.709 --> 18:18.958
in the culture?

18:18.959 --> 18:20.742
Oh, yeah, we are gonna
have to say something.

18:20.743 --> 18:23.458
Oh, you are definitely
gonna have to say something.

18:23.459 --> 18:26.248
Really?

18:26.249 --> 18:31.158
You're going to have to make her
understand about concrete plans,

18:31.159 --> 18:35.918
and-and contingency
plans, and future PLA...

18:35.919 --> 18:37.562
you're just gonna have to explain plans.

18:37.563 --> 18:38.587
Look, I know you're upset

18:38.588 --> 18:40.342
you weren't consulted
about the proposal,

18:40.343 --> 18:42.342
- Yeah! - but now I'm the
one that has to tell her

18:42.343 --> 18:43.686
she's about to screw up her life?

18:43.687 --> 18:45.049
Yes, and now is not a good time

18:45.050 --> 18:46.668
for me to confront my contradictions.

18:46.669 --> 18:50.168
I just need you to stop
this from happening.

18:50.169 --> 18:51.498
Okay, okay, I'll do my best.

18:51.499 --> 18:56.298
I-It is like my entire
history of parental guidance

18:56.299 --> 18:58.708
is-is being erased.

18:58.709 --> 19:00.378
There's no bank.

19:00.379 --> 19:02.588
Nothing that I have done

19:02.589 --> 19:05.758
up to this point matters.

19:05.759 --> 19:07.878
Is this all about Stevie?

19:07.879 --> 19:09.269
Yes! Maybe.

19:11.459 --> 19:12.668
I don't know.

19:12.669 --> 19:14.769
What's going on?

19:15.707 --> 19:17.758
Conrad's looking to replace me.

19:17.759 --> 19:20.519
What?! Says who?

19:22.459 --> 19:23.548
Mike B.

19:23.549 --> 19:26.088
Mike B., come on, that guy

19:26.089 --> 19:29.498
dines out on controversy and bad news.

19:29.499 --> 19:33.758
Yes, and as a result, he
has a jump on everything.

19:33.759 --> 19:35.628
That's got to be some
kind of crazy rumor.

19:35.629 --> 19:37.708
Conrad would never do that to you.

19:37.709 --> 19:38.798
You've been so loyal.

19:38.799 --> 19:41.088
I find it inconceivable
that he would turn on you

19:41.089 --> 19:42.258
like this.

19:42.259 --> 19:44.628
Well, it is Washington

19:44.629 --> 19:48.128
and there is an election coming up,

19:48.129 --> 19:50.399
and the crazy thing is...

19:52.799 --> 19:55.208
...until now, I didn't even realize

19:55.209 --> 19:57.559
how much I've come to love the job.

19:59.919 --> 20:02.269
That's the first time I've
ever heard you say that.

20:05.709 --> 20:07.809
I know.

